23
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,940
=Episode 6=

24
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:56,990
Where exactly do you want to go?

25
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:09,430
What's going on?

26
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,800
It's nothing.

27
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,430
Had a fight with your parents?

28
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,200
Sometimes, I really envy you.

29
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:22,760
It'd be better if I didn't have a dad.

30
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:26,030
Sorry! I shouldn't have said that.

31
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,000
Don't be angry.

32
00:02:31,670 --> 00:02:32,840
Now I kind of understand

33
00:02:33,550 --> 00:02:34,960
why your dad hit you.

34
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,500
Now I realize how selfish

35
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,180
and cold he is!

36
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:39,620
He's like a tyrant,

37
00:02:39,620 --> 00:02:40,820
wanting to control everything.

38
00:02:41,380 --> 00:02:42,220
We're different.

39
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:43,900
Your dad is gone,

40
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:45,100
so he's perfect

41
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,820
in your eyes forever.

42
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,540
You really are

43
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:51,780
bad at talking.

44
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:53,320
No matter what my dad is like,

45
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,220
I still wish he were alive.

46
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,380
I often think,

47
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:03,100
if he were still around,

48
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:05,620
I could be carefree like you,

49
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,140
shouting at him when I'm upset,

50
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,500
being scolded

51
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:12,020
when I fail exams,

52
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,890
someone looking for me
when I skip school to play games,

53
00:03:14,890 --> 00:03:15,740
running away from home

54
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:17,140
when I'm frustrated.

55
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:21,820
As long as he's here.

56
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:28,540
When it comes to envy,

57
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,700
you have no idea how much I envy you.

58
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,500
Envy me?

59
00:03:34,660 --> 00:03:37,100
Did you ever play a game
when you were little?

60
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,020
Your dad would

61
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,660
put his hand

62
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:44,420
just a bit above your head

63
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:45,260
and tell you that

64
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:46,940
if you jumped, you'd reach it.

65
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:49,020
Then you'd keep jumping,

66
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:50,820
and when you almost got there,

67
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:51,980
he'd raise his hand again,

68
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,500
and you'd never reach it.

69
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,780
When I was a kid,

70
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:57,660
my dad loved playing this game with me.

71
00:03:58,660 --> 00:04:00,060
Every time, it would end only when

72
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,180
I cried my eyes out.

73
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,580
Later, I thought

74
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,540
my relationship with him

75
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,580
was just like that game.

76
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:11,260
I would never

77
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:13,220
be able to reach his hand.

78
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,490
But think of it from another angle.

79
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:19,620
Maybe he was trying to motivate you.

80
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:23,060
Let me tell you a story.

81
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,380
When I was six,

82
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:27,260
I remember it very clearly.

83
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:29,660
My dad took me
to the natural history museum

84
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:31,140
and kept

85
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:32,580
telling me what each dinosaur was

86
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:34,660
and what era everything was from.

87
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:35,940
Fine,

88
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:37,380
he's a genius,

89
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:38,660
he knows everything.

90
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,260
A lot of people

91
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:41,860
followed us,

92
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:43,380
thinking he was a tour guide.

93
00:04:44,570 --> 00:04:45,930
I was happy to listen.

94
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,700
Then, suddenly, he stopped,

95
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:48,820
looked at me seriously,

96
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:49,660
and asked,

97
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:50,850
"Tell me,

98
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:51,810
what did I just say?"

99
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,580
How could I remember?

100
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,900
He exploded,

101
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:00,580
yelling at me in front of everyone,
calling me a fool

102
00:05:00,580 --> 00:05:01,620
and an idiot!

103
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:03,340
He pointed at me and said,

104
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:04,540
"How can a stupid kid

105
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:05,620
like you be my child?"

106
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:09,340
Then he walked away.

107
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:11,860
All I could think was,

108
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:13,580
"That's it.

109
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:14,980
My dad doesn't want me anymore.

110
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:16,900
I'll end up begging on the street

111
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,740
like he said."

112
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,860
That's just adults messing with kids.

113
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:21,860
No!

114
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,760
He's been like that since I was little.

115
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:25,860
If I didn't do something right,

116
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:26,700
he'd say,

117
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:27,860
"If you can't even do this,

118
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,440
you'll be begging on the street one day."

119
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:31,020
I really thought

120
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:32,180
I'd end up begging.

121
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:36,380
Later that day, my mom picked me up.

122
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,540
How bad

123
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:41,940
is my life, huh?

124
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,380
I didn't realize

125
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:47,260
your dad was so harsh.

126
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,580
He's more than harsh.

127
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:52,900
It's late.

128
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:53,980
Let's go home.

129
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:54,960
If you don't go back now,

130
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:56,380
when your dad sees you, he will…

131
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,100
He will what?

132
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,140
Let's go.

133
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,980
(Jinxiu Garden)

134
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:11,220
We're here.

135
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:12,940
Hurry back.

136
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,350
Xiao Han,

137
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,100
your dad must love you so much,

138
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,260
way more than my dad

139
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:28,460
ever loved me.

140
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:57,100
(Shanghai Puyang No. 2 Middle School)

141
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:00,860
He really slapped you?

142
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:06,260
Where did you go

143
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:07,380
